107: 2026-04-15: Made slide-to-top animation springy by switching from `duration-500 ease-out` to `duration-700 ease-[cubic-bezier(0.34,1.56,0.64,1)]` — the 1.56 overshoot control point creates a bounce-past-settle spring feel.

2026-04-16: Conducted a targeted backend reliability review of current uncommitted changes (`jobcarbon.py`, `jobcarbon_api.py`, `tests/`). Findings: no material P0/P1 issues; malformed JSON now degrades via `HTTPRequestError` and stage-level warning capture, extractor failures are isolated by `run_extraction_stage`, and Teamtailor/Breezy detection broadening appears correct for tested URL shapes. Residual risk accepted for now: request-budget cap is soft because `BudgetedSession` enforces a 1.0s minimum per call, so end-to-end runtime can slightly exceed nominal remaining budget near exhaustion.

- 2026-04-16: Final-pass code review of uncommitted backend diff (`jobcarbon.py`, `jobcarbon_api.py`, `tests/test_jobcarbon_unit.py`, `tests/test_jobcarbon_integration.py`, `tests/test_jobcarbon_api.py`) found no remaining P0-P2 issues. Verified runtime/fallback correctness, malformed JSON degradation (`HTTPRequestError` -> stage warnings / API 502 `upstream_payload_error`), timeout-budget gating paths, and Teamtailor/Breezy detection broadening. Re-ran focused suite: 68 tests passed. Residual non-blocking risk remains: overall budget cap is soft due to 1.0s minimum call deadline in `HTTPSession.get`.
2026-04-16: Completed backend reliability hardening for production ATS variability. Chose stage-level failure isolation (`run_extraction_stage`) plus defensive JSON parsing (`fetch_json` wrapping decode failures as `HTTPRequestError`) to prevent malformed upstream payloads from surfacing as 500s. Added API normalization for these upstream parsing failures (`502 upstream_payload_error`) rather than generic internal errors.
2026-04-16: Added request-budget controls (`RequestBudget`, `BudgetedSession`) and platform-aware fallback gating. Also bounded `HTTPSession.get` retries/backoff by per-call deadline to avoid runaway latencies. Kept comparison fallbacks for most direct platforms unless credible direct signal plus comparison evidence exists; special-cased SuccessFactors to skip expensive comparison fallbacks once credible direct evidence is present.
2026-04-16: Broadened detection robustness: Teamtailor now detects locale and single-segment numeric-slug URLs, and Breezy now detects `*.breezy.hr` subdomains (not only `jobs.breezy.hr`).
2026-04-16: Validated with full unit/integration/API suite (`68` tests passing) and live ATS sweep across 24 ATS buckets using real company pages where available. Observed 0 exceptions; iCIMS Peraton no longer throws parser-style 500 and now degrades to warnings with successful response.
2026-04-16: Promoted reliability hardening to production via commit `023ffa6` on `main` and Railway deployment `6f561952-cda9-4706-b331-8e8751d75ca6` (SUCCESS). Post-deploy smoke checks on `https://api.howoldisthisjob.com` confirm health endpoint OK and expected estimate behavior: iCIMS Peraton now succeeds with warning (no 500), SuccessFactors succeeds, Teamtailor succeeds, and Workday/ADP return expected `no_date`.
2026-04-16: Adjusted homepage "move up" UX to prevent two-phase snapping and card-induced upward jumps. Replaced translateY-based wrapper animation with a `padding-top` transition on `<main>` keyed to `data-has-history`/loading state, so vertical repositioning begins immediately on submit and settles once. Replaced native `<details>` sections in `ResultCard` with controlled toggle buttons to avoid browser default summary/details layout behavior causing abrupt reflow perceptions during card interaction.
2026-04-16: Investigated screenshot-reported Claude startup JSON error. Verified `~/.claude.json` is valid UTF-8 JSON (no BOM/NUL; Python parser succeeds) and CLI no longer fails at parse stage in this environment; current blocking error is authentication (`401 Invalid authentication credentials`). Chosen remediation path is config reset only if parse error reappears, otherwise re-authenticate account/session.
2026-04-16: Removed padding-top transition animation from <main> in page.tsx that caused layout shift. Previously, clicking 'Check' triggered data-has-history=true (via loading state) which fired pt-[24vh]→pt-6 CSS transition, shifting the entire block (logo+title+form) abruptly upward. Fix: removed has-[[data-has-history]]:pt-6, md:has-[[data-has-history]]:pt-8, transition-[padding-top], duration-500, and ease-[...] classes from main. Now padding-top is static at pt-[24vh]/md:pt-[25vh] — content stays anchored, results grow below, no layout shift or dropdown-expansion jank.
2026-04-16: Fixed main content centering in page.tsx — changed from justify-start+pt-[24vh] to justify-center+py-12. With min-h-[calc(100svh-56px)] and justify-center, content is pixel-perfect centered when page is short (no results) and naturally flows top-aligned when results make the page tall. Started local Python API (jobcarbon-api) via PM2 on port 8000 to fix 'could not load history' error that appeared when backend was not running locally.
2026-04-16: Rebuilt the about page around scannable structural blocks (short hero + numbered signals card + platform status table + chevron FAQ accordion) after user rejected the prior prose-heavy layout. Chose a monochrome data-table treatment over the previous brand-colored chip grid because it surfaces three real statuses (Supported / Blocked / No dates) rather than implying parity across platforms; brand colors still live on the result card and home-page platform carousel. Used `<details>` + Tailwind `group-open:rotate-180` for the FAQ chevron so the page stays a server component (no client JS). User approved: "the about page is good."
2026-04-16: Documented Greenhouse original-date ceiling. Public boards API (`boards-api.greenhouse.io/v1/boards/{org}/jobs/{id}`) returns only `first_published` + `updated_at`, both scoped to the current `job_id`. Reposts create new IDs and reset `first_published`; there is no cross-ID lineage, no prior-version pointer, and no board-transfer history exposed. Treating `first_published` as high-reliability "posted" is correct for the current record but cannot recover the true original posting date when a role has been re-requisitioned. UI repost warning (`detect_repost` jobcarbon.py:3079) is the right mitigation; no code change warranted.
2026-04-17: Polished `progress-pipeline.tsx` per user feedback — dropped the `uppercase tracking-[0.12em]` styling on the "Checking · {platform}" header (user explicitly said "NEVER do capitalized text like that"), bumped the header from `text-xs` to `text-[13px]` to match stage rows, and tightened the card from `p-4`/`gap-3`/`gap-1.5` to `px-3 py-2.5`/`gap-2`/`gap-1`. Highlight logic (running stage gets spinner, completed gets check) was already correct; only visual density and casing changed.
2026-04-17: Removed `html { overflow-y: scroll }` from `site/src/app/globals.css`. Reserving a permanent scrollbar track was visible as a hollow strip on the right edge on macOS Chrome, and became very obvious when the confirm-modal backdrop dimmed the page but stopped short of that gutter. Trade-off accepted: Windows classic-scrollbar users may see a small horizontal shift when content transitions from non-overflowing to overflowing — the previous always-visible gutter was the worse visual on the default (macOS) target.
2026-04-17: Reverted the no-reservation approach because it introduced an equally-bad shift when content grew to overflow. Replaced with three coordinated fixes: (1) `html { scrollbar-gutter: stable }` reserves gutter space without rendering a visible track (cleaner than the old `overflow-y: scroll`), (2) `html { background: var(--background) }` forces the reserved gutter to paint the same white as `body`, so the strip is invisible when no scrollbar is shown, and (3) `.gel-dialog-overlay { width: 100vw; left: 0 }` extends the modal dim over the reserved gutter so the backdrop doesn't leave an undimmed strip when a dialog is open.
2026-04-17: Even with `scrollbar-gutter: stable` + white html bg, Chrome macOS still tinted the reserved gutter slightly (its default track is painted even when no thumb is shown), producing a visible lighter strip under the confirm-modal dim. Fix: explicitly style the scrollbar via `scrollbar-color: #d4d4d4 transparent` (Firefox/standard) and `::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: transparent }` + custom rounded thumb (Chrome/Safari). Track is transparent, so the reserved gutter reads as page bg under dim; thumb only shows when actually scrolling. Rejected alternatives: `scrollbar-gutter: stable both-edges` (adds a matching strip on the left — worse), removing gutter reservation (reintroduces the horizontal shift the user already vetoed).
2026-04-19: Created the Sentry Python project (`dhiyaan/jobcarbon-api`) via REST API rather than asking the user to click through the Sentry UI — the user supplied a broader user-auth token (`sntryu_...`) after the wizard's narrowly-scoped token failed `team:read`. Path: `POST /api/0/teams/dhiyaan/dhiyaan/projects/` with body `{name, slug, platform: "python"}`, then `GET /api/0/projects/dhiyaan/jobcarbon-api/keys/` to fetch the DSN. Pushed `SENTRY_DSN` and `SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=production` to Railway via `railway variables --set`. Then deploy failed silently (Sentry was loaded, never installed): Railpack's Python provider on Railway runs `python3 <script>` directly and does NOT pip-install from `pyproject.toml`'s `dependencies` field — it requires a `requirements.txt`. Added one (single line `sentry-sdk>=2.17`); next build picked it up and installed `sentry-sdk-2.58.0`. Healthcheck recovered. Lesson for future Python deps on this Railway project: maintain `requirements.txt` as the source of truth, not `pyproject.toml`.
2026-04-19: Wired Sentry into both surfaces after user signed up. Frontend: `@sentry/wizard -i nextjs` ran clean inside `site/`, creating the standard Next 16 instrumentation layout (server/edge/client configs + `src/instrumentation.ts`). Deleted the wizard's `/sentry-example-page` and `/api/sentry-example-api` scaffolding because they're test artifacts, not production surface. Dropped `tracesSampleRate` from `1` → `0.1` in all three site configs to protect the Developer-tier 10k performance-units/mo quota — at 100% sampling even light traffic would exhaust it. Backend: chose a defensive init (`try: import sentry_sdk`; init only if `SENTRY_DSN` is set) so the module still imports cleanly locally without the dep and without a DSN; added explicit `capture_exception` calls in both `except Exception` fallbacks (sync HTTP handler and SSE stream handler) because stdlib `BaseHTTPRequestHandler` swallows handler exceptions and Sentry's default `sys.excepthook` wouldn't see them. `SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN` pushed to Vercel production only — Preview env add needs an interactive "all branches?" confirmation that stdin-pipe didn't satisfy; deferred. Declined to install the Sentry MCP server (user rejected).
2026-04-19: Shipped SEO + security headers + Vercel Analytics as one slice. Used Next.js app-router metadata files (`app/robots.ts`, `app/sitemap.ts`) instead of static files in `public/` so the URLs are derived from a single source and TypeScript-checked. For headers, deliberately skipped a strict `script-src`/`style-src` CSP because Sentry's `/monitoring` tunnel route + Vercel Analytics + Tailwind hashed styles would all need nonce middleware to coexist with a strict policy — too much risk for too little gain on a static content site. Kept just `frame-ancestors 'none'` (clickjacking protection that pairs with `X-Frame-Options: DENY`) plus the standard four sniff/referrer/permissions headers. HSTS already provided by Vercel. Vercel Analytics pulled in via `@vercel/analytics/next` (v2.0.1) — free tier, automatic on Vercel deploys, no env vars.

2026-04-19: After user added `Zone Settings:Edit` scope to the Cloudflare API token, flipped Always Use HTTPS, Automatic HTTPS Rewrites, and Brotli via `PATCH /zones/{zone_id}/settings/{setting}`. Bot Fight Mode rejected the same token with `code 10000 Authentication error` because `/zones/{zone_id}/bot_management` is gated on Account-level Bot Management auth, not Zone Settings — Cloudflare separates these even on free zones. User can flip Bot Fight Mode manually in the dashboard. Verified `http://howoldisthisjob.com` now returns 301 to https.

2026-04-19: User asked what is left to reach "production level." Framed the answer as a hardening backlog (site + API already live) rather than a re-architecture, and ordered it Blockers → Reliability/observability → Polish so the user can pick a wedge. Blockers surfaced: 17 uncommitted files + untracked `progress-pipeline.tsx`, missing `/privacy` and `/terms` (required by the HttpOnly `jobcarbon_session` cookie), no API rate limiting, and missing `robots.txt`/`sitemap.xml`. Reliability gaps: no Sentry, no uptime alerts beyond Railway restart policy, CI only runs `py_compile + unittest`, no frontend tests, no security headers. Polish gaps: no analytics, no URL-lookup response cache, no recent a11y/Lighthouse pass. No code change this turn — awaiting user's pick on which slice to start with.
2026-04-21: Verified Chrome extension state. API /healthz ok on api.howoldisthisjob.com; batch-estimate returns success for lever. Playwright smoke subset (lever-detail, greenhouse-detail, ashby-detail, ashby-list) all passing in 15.8s with headless Chromium persistent context + load-extension. Extension code paths (content.js list/detail badge injection + background.js batch proxy) functional against prod.
2026-04-21: Redesigned extension UI. Replaced gradient gel-calendar logo-badge.svg with a minimal outlined calendar glyph (24-viewBox, 1.75 stroke, brand blue #257cff) — the old icon was unreadable at 16px. Rewrote content.css: rounded-square chips (6px radius, not pill), 22–24px tall, site tokens (#e5e5e5 border / #fff surface / #111 fg), prefers-color-scheme dark variant. Detail card (iCIMS/BrassRing fallback) gained a calendar icon + two-line hierarchy so it shares the visual language of the pill. 24/24 full smoke still passes; 4-case subset re-verified after changes. Content.js: added <img class="jobcarbon-detail-card__icon"> and wrapped title+meta in .jobcarbon-detail-card__body.

2026-04-21: Bumped site deps (next 16.2.4, react/react-dom 19.2.5). Build clean.
2026-04-21: Fixed Next.js 16 script-in-component error by moving theme-init to next/script strategy="beforeInteractive".
2026-04-21: Fixed hydration error by removing body.classList mutation from pre-hydration theme script and adding suppressHydrationWarning to <body>. Tailwind dark variants already key off <html> so body toggle was redundant.
